screen_name: After a couple of days the pains seemed to leave but i was still left tired. Now at the end of the 7 days staying locked in my daughters pink room im still a bit fatigued, those 7 days are just a guide definitely.

The fever hit bad on Friday and i dont remember much of Friday at all. Saturday was up and down all day managed to drive myself through to Dundee to get tested. By Sunday the fever seemed to have left but i felt sore all over and wanted to sleep all the time.

However several of the days i was out the game one whole day with horrendous fever. It started with a mild tickle in my throat, dismissed as their was no cough, last Thursday night i started to feel feverish and started to cough regularly.

So i got tested on Saturday for Covid-19 through my work waited two days for result and found out i was positive.(No sympathy unless in cake form) Luckily for me it was a mild case probably caught at work.
